# ‚òùüèº Note
- When adding and removing values at the beginning and end of a TypeScript array, it can be difficult to remember which method does what. Here are some tips:
- Unshift and shift move the entire array sideways (by adding and removing elements at the beginning)
- Push and Pop do NOT move the array sideways (because they add and remove elements at the end)
- A very simple mnemonic would be:
    - For the pairs Push/Pop and Unshift/Shift, the method with more letters extends the array
    - Push/Pop - Push has more letters than Pop = Push adds element(s) to the array; Pop removes element(s)
    - Unshift/Shift - Unshift has more letters than Shift = Unshift adds element(s) to the array, Shift removes element(s)

